HEADWORD: Moonflower
<hw>Moon"flow`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The oxeye daisy; -- called also <altname>moon
daisy</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A kind of morning glory
(<spn>Ipomoea Bona-nox</spn>) with large white flowers opening at
night.</def>⟦br⟧
